Diagnosis.
Odo patricius
can be distinguished from other species by the male palp, which has short and conical RTA, acute at the apex (
Figs 3–4
). The female epigynal plate has a narrow atrium with posterior extensions that are very elongated and enlarged at tip (
Fig. 5
), and small and rounded spermathecae (
Fig. 6
).
